                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/8–2144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-21T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 21, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 21—3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6763. Comea 75. The Russian Ambassador just called and left me a letter<note
                        n="26" xml:id="d149fn26">Not printed.</note> stating that his Government has
                    resolved to confirm the terms of unconditional surrender for Germany agreed and
                    signed by the European Advisory Commission on July 25.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
